import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

#   iterations = 100_000
iterations = 1_000_000

#    delta = 0.001
delta = 0.001

#      
def function(a, b, c, m, gamma, x_0=0.7, y_0=0.1, z_0=0.4):
    print(f' : x_0 = {x_0}, y_0 = {y_0}, z_0 = {z_0}, a = {a}, b = {b}, c = {c}, m = {m}')
    print(f' gamma = {gamma},   {round((gamma/b) * 100, 2)}%  b')

    X, Y, Z = [x_0], [y_0], [z_0]
    for k in range(1, iterations):
        X.append(X[k-1] - delta*X[k-1] + delta*X[k-1]*Y[k-1])
        Y.append(Y[k-1] + delta*Y[k-1] - delta*Y[k-1]*X[k-1] + delta*a*Y[k-1]*Y[k-1] - delta*Y[k-1]*Z[k-1])
        Z.append(Z[k-1] + b*delta - gamma*delta - delta*m*(c-Y[k-1])*Z[k-1])
    
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16, 9))
    
    ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 1, projection = '3d')
    ax.plot(X, Y, Z, linewidth=0.4, c="red")
    ax.set_xlabel('X ( )', fontsize=14)
    ax.set_ylabel('Y ( )', fontsize=14)
    ax.set_zlabel('Z ( )', fontsize=14)
    ax.set_title('')

    X, Y, Z = [x_0], [y_0], [z_0]
    for k in range(1, iterations):
        X.append(X[k-1] - delta*X[k-1] + delta*X[k-1]*Y[k-1])
        Y.append(Y[k-1] + delta*Y[k-1] - delta*Y[k-1]*X[k-1] + delta*a*Y[k-1]*Y[k-1] - delta*Y[k-1]*Z[k-1])
        Z.append(Z[k-1] + b*delta - delta*m*(c-Y[k-1])*Z[k-1])
    
    ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 2, projection='3d')
    ax.plot(X, Y, Z, linewidth=0.4)
    ax.set_xlabel('X ( )', fontsize=14)
